---
title: Pineapple Chicken for Dinner with Southwestern Burritos for Lunch
description: Cook it once, eat it twice: tonight’s dinner extras transform into tomorrow’s lunch. That’s thanks to special added ingredients that can easily be heated up, even at the office (your coworkers will be amazed, trust us). The night before, the Southwest-spiced chicken, sliced poblanos with onion, and warm pineapple top a sweet and savory rice bowl. The next day, the leftover ingredients are tucked into a quick burrito that you’ll be proud to show off to your workmates. *The Lunch Burrito information is as follows: Calories: 710, Fat: 25 g, Saturated Fat: 12 g, Carbohydrate: 61 g, Sugar: 2 g, Fiber: 3 g, Protein: 48 g, Cholesterol: 170 mg, Sodium: 960 mg. The nutrition facts panel below represents the nutrient values for the Pineapple Chicken Dinner
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/2018w49-r12-61ec372c.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/2018w49-r12-5bc9f0b4ae08b505ab6f0d22-266bf9ff.pdf
time required: 40 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/pineapple-chicken-for-dinner-5bc9f0b4ae08b505ab6f0d22
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 670 kcal
  fat: 22 g
  saturated fat: 8 g
  carbohydrates: 74 g
  sugar: 13 g
  protein: 41 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 200 mg
servings: 2
course: main course
author: Sara Heilman
---

Wash and dry all produce. Core, seed, and thinly slice @Poblano Pepper{2}(sliced thin). Halve, peel, and thinly slice @Red Onion{1}(sliced thin). Mince a few slices until you have 1 TBSP. Drain @Pineapple{4%oz}, reserving juice. Finely chop @Roma Tomato{1}(finely chopped). Roughly chop @Cilantro{¼%oz}(roughly chopped). Zest, then quarter @Lime{1}(quartered). Place @Jasmine Rice{¾%cup} and 1 ¼ cups water in a #small lidded pot{}. Cover and bring to a boil, then reduce heat to a gentle simmer. Cook until tender, about ~{15%minutes}. Keep covered until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine tomato, minced onion, half the cilantro, 1 TBSP pineapple juice, juice from two lime quarters, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. In a separate small bowl, stir together 4 TBSP @Sour Cream{8%tbsp} (2 packages) and a pinch of @Chipotle Powder{1%tsp}. Add water, 1 tsp at a time, until mixture has a drizzling consistency. Season with salt and more chipotle powder to taste.

Pat @Chicken Breasts{24%oz} dry with a #paper towel{}. Season all over with @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tbsp}, a small pinch of chipotle powder, salt, and @pepper{}. Heat a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{4%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium heat (use a nonstick pan if you have one). Add chicken and cook until brown and cooked through, about ~{8%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest.

Meanwhile, in a separate large pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Add pineapple and cook, stirring, until browned, ~{3-5%minutes}. Transfer to a #plate{}. Heat another drizzle of olive oil in same pan. Add poblano, sliced onion, and a big pinch of salt. Cook, stirring, until softened, about ~{5%minutes}. Remove from heat.

Slice chicken. Fluff rice with a #fork{}, then stir in lime zest and 1 TBSP @Butter{1%tbsp}. Season with salt and pepper. Set aside ½ cup rice for lunch, then divide remainder between bowls for dinner. Top with pineapple and half the chicken. Reserve ½ cup poblano mixture for lunch, then spoon remainder onto bowls along with salsa, crema, and remaining cilantro. Serve with remaining lime quarters on the side.

In the morning, divide reserved rice, chicken, and veggie mixture among @Flour Tortillas{2}. Sprinkle with @Mexican Cheese Blend{½%cup}. Roll into wraps and pack each with sour cream. When ready to eat, microwave until warm, about ~{15%seconds}. Enjoy with sour cream for dipping.

> The Lunch Burrito: Calories 710, Fat 25g, Saturated Fat 12g, Carbohydrate 61g, Sugar 2g, Fiber 3g, Protein 48g, Cholesterol 170mg, Sodium 960mg. The nutrition facts represent the Pineapple Chicken Dinner.